# Learned Memory

## Learned User Preferences

- Always respond in Korean
- Daily briefings and summaries should be in Korean
- All generated documents (DOCX, PPTX, markdown reviews) must be entirely in Korean — headings, labels, section titles, bullet points, and conclusions included
- English is allowed only for proper nouns and technical terms with no standard Korean translation
- Plans and skill definitions (SKILL.md) should be written in English when explicitly requested ("영어로 계획해줘")
- Content must be substantive and detailed, never skeleton or template-only output
- Slack notifications go to `#효정-할일` channel (ID: `C0AA8NT4T8T`) — never send to DM
- Slack posts use threaded replies: main summary first, then individual items in thread
- After creating or modifying a skill, always test it end-to-end and fix issues before declaring done
- When creating a new skill, also create the corresponding Cursor command if one doesn't exist
- When Notion API cannot upload binary files (DOCX/PPTX), adapt content as structured sub-pages instead
- Subagent-generated files must be verified after completion — missing output files are a pipeline failure

## Learned Workspace Facts

- `paper-review` skill: 8-phase pipeline (Ingest → Review → PM Analysis → DOCX → PPTX → NLM Slides → Notion → Slack)
- `related-papers-scout` skill: finds 5 hot related papers from top institutions and posts to Slack with thread-per-paper
- Paper review and related-papers-scout Slack channel: `#deep-research` (ID: `C0A6X68LTN1`)
- EOD Ship Report Slack channel: `#효정-할일` (ID: `C0AA8NT4T8T`) — report must be in Korean
- Paper review outputs: `outputs/papers/{id}-{perspective}-{DATE}.md`, `outputs/papers/{id}-analysis-{DATE}.docx`, `outputs/presentations/{id}-presentation-{DATE}.pptx`
- Default Notion parent page for paper reviews: `3209eddc34e6801b8921f55d85153730` (ThakiCloud 논문 리뷰)
- Notion API does not support pipe tables — convert to bulleted lists or HTML table blocks
- Node.js scripts for DOCX/PPTX generation need `NODE_PATH=$(npm root -g)` to resolve globally installed packages
- Phase 3 subagents must use the Write tool to persist their markdown outputs — they do not auto-save
- NotebookLM MCP requires absolute paths for all file operations
- Slack file upload uses the 3-step flow: `getUploadURLExternal` → POST file → `completeUploadExternal`
- The git-push-pull `tmp` branch rule applies ONLY to `ai-platform-webui`, not this repo
